	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Augusta</placeName> <date>Nove 29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">My Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">enclosed<lb/> you find an order on <persName>Mayer Haas</persName> &#38;c<lb/> for forty two 24&#47;100 Doll a part of <sic>colections</sic><lb/> that I have made for you as follows<lb/> <persName>Mess Caro</persName> &#38; <persName>Blascoer</persName> for 2 sets of the<lb/> five book <persName>moses</persName> 15 30.00</p>
				<p>2 fine prayer books sent to my</p>
				<table rows="5" cols="3">
				<row>
				<cell>order</cell>
				<cell>5</cell>
				<cell>10.00</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>one prayer book &#8220;</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell><hi rend="underline">  2.50</hi></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell/>
				<cell/>
				<cell>42.50</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell/>
				<cell/>
				<cell><hi rend="underline">   21</hi></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>paid &#189; 00 exchange</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell>&#36;42.29</cell>
				</row>
				</table>
				<p>for above please acknowledge reced<lb/> <persName>Mr Morritz Schwarz</persName> has also subscribed<lb/> for one year to your <sic>Occitend</sic> you<lb/> will please forward the same to<lb/> <persName>M Schwarz</persName> <placeName>Augusta Ga</placeName></p>
				<p><persName>Mr M Jacobs</persName> of <placeName>Athens</placeName> made complaint to<lb/> me in regard that he has received but<lb/> 2 No of his <sic>Occidtent</sic> &#38; has subscribed<lb/> at the time when you were in our<lb/> city last news we have but little our<lb/> congregation is coming on slow although<lb/> our <add>Hebrew</add> <persName>Mr I Schatz</persName> is well beliked &#38;<lb/> fully deserves it&#44; He is a gentleman that<lb/> haves<add>&#63;</add> a good <sic>caracter</sic> but he is not</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>able to <sic>Legtur</sic> which is very much<lb/> wanting in a place like ours.  I have<lb/> a great trouble to get <add>Hebrew</add> on <date><sic>Sabath</sic></date> &#38;<lb/> the fact is if they should not improve<lb/> in a short time in religious feeling<lb/> I fear nothing will remain but the<lb/> name.  My intention is to move to<lb/> your city next fall&#44; where I hope<lb/> to hear your valuable <sic>Legtures</sic> on<lb/> many occasion.  I do it also more<lb/> on account of my children as I<lb/> wish to <sic>rase</sic> them like Jews&#44; I am<lb/> satisfied in our place&#44; there never<lb/> will be done anything to our children<lb/> please let me hear from you soon<lb/> <persName>Mrs Mayer</persName> sends her best respects<lb/> to you also <persName>Mrs Lambert</persName>.<lb/>  and accept the same from your<lb/> most truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Isaac Mayer</persName></p>
		</body>
